<TEXT>
The captain of a ship which was near the sinking Titanic in 1912 could have
done nothing to save the 1,490 people who died, an official UK inquiry
concluded. But it criticised Captain Stanley Lord (left) for not responding
to the luxury liner's distress signals. Capt Lord, censured by a 1912
inquiry, died in 1962 but supporters have fought to clear his name.
